Name: Saddle
Desc: Land connecting two high points

Name: Cave
Desc: Natural underground space large enough for a human to enter

Name: Ravine
Desc: Small valley, often due to stream erosion

Name: Rift Valley
Desc: Linear lowland created by a tectonic rift or fault

Name: Hill
Desc: Landform that extends above the surrounding terrain

Name: Knoll
Desc: Small hill

Name: Flat
Desc: Relatively level surface of land within a region of greater relief

Name: Plateau
Desc: Highland area, usually of relatively flat terrain

Name: Impact Crater
Desc: Circular depression on a solid astronomical body formed by a smaller object's impact

Name: Waterfall
Desc: Natural river formation

Name: Watershed
Desc: Area of land where precipitation collects and drains off into a common outlet

Name: Sinkhole
Desc: Geologically-formed topological depression

Name: Butte
Desc: Isolated hill with steep, often vertical sides and a small, relatively flat top

Name: Gulch
Desc: Deep V-shaped valley formed by erosion

Name: Lava Spine
Desc: Vertical growth of solid volcanic lava

Name: Gorge
Desc: Deep ravine between cliffs

Name: Supervolcano
Desc: Volcano that has erupted 1000 cubic km of lava in a single eruption

Name: Stream
Desc: Body of surface water flowing down a channel

Name: Terrace
Desc: A step-like landform

Name: Mud Volcano
Desc: Landform created by the eruption of mud or slurries, water and gases

Name: Ridge
Desc: Chain of mountains or hills that form a continuous elevated crest for some distance

Name: Mesa
Desc: Elevated area of land with a flat top and sides that are usually steep cliffs

Name: Volcanic Crater
Desc: Roughly circular depression in the ground caused by volcanic activity

Name: Lava Dome
Desc: Roughly circular protrusion from slowly extruded viscous volcanic lava

Name: Gully
Desc: Landform created by running water and/or mass movement eroding sharply into soil

Name: Arroyo
Desc: Dry creek or stream bed with flow after rain

Name: River Island
Desc: Exposed land within a river.

Name: Quarry
Desc: A place from which a geological material has been excavated from the ground

Name: Plain
Desc: Expanse of land which is mostly flat and treeless

Name: Anabranch
Desc: A section of a river or stream that diverts from the main channel and rejoins it downstream.

Name: Lake
Desc: Large body of relatively still water

Name: Summit
Desc: Point on a surface with a higher elevation than all immediately adjacent points

Name: KÄ«puka
Desc: Area of land surrounded by one or more younger lava flows

Name: Pseudocrater
Desc: Pseudocraters are formed by steam explosions as flowing hot lava crosses over a wet surface, such as a swamp, a lake, or a pond.

Name: Vale
Desc: Low area between hills, often with a river running through it

Name: Lava Lake
Desc: Molten lava contained in a volcanic crater

Name: Bayou
Desc: French term for a body of water typically found in flat, low-lying area

Name: Corrie
Desc: An amphitheatre-like valley formed by glacial erosion or cwm

Name: Dune
Desc: Hill of loose sand built by aeolian processes or the flow of water

Name: Abyssal Plain
Desc: Flat area on the deep ocean floor

Name: Floodplain
Desc: Land adjacent to a river which is flooded during periods of high discharge

Name: Volcano Complex
Desc: Landform of more than one related volcanic centre

Name: Hoodoo
Desc: Tall, thin spire of relatively soft rock usually topped by harder rock

Name: Mountain Pass
Desc: Route through a mountain range or over a ridge

Name: Salt Marsh
Desc: Coastal ecosystem between land and open saltwater that is regularly flooded

Name: Oceanic Plateau
Desc: Relatively flat submarine region that rises well above the level of the ambient seabed

Name: Submarine Volcano
Desc: Underwater vents or fissures in the Earth's surface from which magma can erupt

Name: Volcanic Island
Desc: Island of volcanic origin

Name: Volcano
Desc: Rupture in the crust of a planet that allows lava, ash, and gases to escape from below the surface

Name: Tidal Marsh
Desc: Marsh subject to tidal change in water

Name: Wetland
Desc: Land area that is permanently or seasonally saturated with water

Name: Strandflat
Desc: Type of landform found in high-latitude areas

Name: Atoll
Desc: Ring-shaped coral reef

Name: Coral Reef
Desc: Outcrop of rock in the sea formed by the growth and deposit of stony coral skeletons

Name: Shoal
Desc: Natural submerged sandbank that rises from a body of water to near the surface

Name: Salt Pan
Desc: Flat expanse of ground covered with salt and other minerals (salt flat)

Name: Oceanic Ridge
Desc: An underwater mountain system formed by plate tectonic spreading

Name: Glacier Cave
Desc: Cave formed within the ice of a glacier

Name: Island
Desc: Any piece of sub-continental land that is surrounded by water

Name: Cove
Desc: Small sheltered bay or coastal inlet

Name: Sea Cave
Desc: Cave formed by the wave action of the sea and located along present or former coastlines

Name: Lagoon
Desc: Shallow body of water separated from a larger body of water by a narrow landform

Name: Delta, River
Desc: Silt deposition landform at the mouth of a river

Name: Fjord
Desc: Long, narrow inlet with steep sides or cliffs, created by glacial activity
